# MMS Demo Application

**Metro Fleet Mileage Management System** - Win-the-bid demonstration application.

## Overview

This is a demonstration application for Metro fleet preventive maintenance (PM) management. It showcases CSV-based PM projection over a 10-year horizon with an infinite canvas interface using semantic zoom levels (strategic → tactical → operational views).

**Key Features:**
- Drag-and-drop PM rescheduling with constraint validation
- "Bow-wave" risk visualization (fleet maintenance clustering)
- WebGL-powered infinite canvas rendering with deck.gl
- State management with @belt/tools

## Getting Started

```bash
# Install dependencies
bun install

# Start development server
bun dev

# Build for production
bun run build

# Lint code
bun run lint

# Format code
bun run format
```

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── main.tsx              # Entry point
├── App.tsx               # Root component
├── store/                # @belt/tools state machines
├── engine/               # PM projection algorithm (CRITICAL)
├── import/               # CSV parsing and validation
├── canvas/               # deck.gl infinite canvas
├── components/           # React UI components
├── types/                # TypeScript interfaces
└── utils/                # Helpers

public/sample-data/       # Sample CSV files for testing
docs/                     # 9-part specification (MMS_SPEC_001-009)
```

---

## @belt/tools Utilities Reference

The `@belt/tools` package provides comprehensive utilities for state management, runtime validation, and common operations. All utilities are already available in this project.

### State Machine

Immer-based reactive state management with React hooks and automatic cache management.

#### Creating Slices

```typescript
import { createSlice, createAsyncSlice, createMachine } from '@belt/tools';

// Synchronous slice for local state
const fleetSlice = createSlice({
  id: 'fleet',
  initial: {
    trains: [],
    pmHistory: [],
    selectedTrain: null as string | null,
  },
  cache: { policy: 'session' }, // or 'public', 'private'
  reducers: {
    importFleet: (state, payload: Train[]) => {
      state.trains = payload; // Immer allows direct mutations
    },
    selectTrain: (state, trainId: string) => {
      state.selectedTrain = trainId;
    },
    clearSelection: (state) => {
      state.selectedTrain = null;
    },
  },
});

// Async slice for data fetching
const analyticsSlice = createAsyncSlice({
  id: 'analytics',
  cache: {
    policy: 'public',
    ttl: '5m', // Time-to-live using ms() format
    swr: true, // Stale-while-revalidate
  },
  context: {},
  load: async () => {
    const response = await fetch('/api/analytics');
    return response.json();
  },
});
```

#### Creating Machines

```tsx
import { createMachine } from '@belt/tools';

const appMachine = createMachine({
  id: 'mms',
  slices: {
    fleet: fleetSlice,
    analytics: analyticsSlice,
  },
  context: { userId: null }, // Global context
});

// Use in React components
function FleetView() {
  const { state, actions } = appMachine.useMachine('fleet');

  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={() => actions.importFleet(trains)}>
        Import Fleet
      </button>
      <div>{state.trains.length} trains loaded</div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Cache Policies:**
- `public` - Shared cache, TTL-based invalidation
- `private` - User-specific cache, invalidated on user change
- `session` - Session-specific cache, invalidated on app restart

---

### Runtime Schema Validation

Type-safe runtime validation using TypeBox with concise syntax.

#### Basic Types

```typescript
import { createType, createSchema, isType, invariantType, InferType } from '@belt/tools';

// Primitive types
const StringType = createType('string');
const NumberType = createType('number');
const BooleanType = createType('boolean');
const DateType = createType('date');

// Optional types (append ?)
const OptionalString = createType('string?');
const OptionalNumber = createType('number?');

// Array types (append [])
const StringArray = createType('string[]');
const NumberArray = createType('number[]');

// Type guards
if (isType(value, 'string')) {
  console.log(value.toUpperCase()); // TypeScript knows it's string
}

if (isType(value, 'date')) {
  console.log(value.toISOString()); // TypeScript knows it's Date
}
```

#### Object Schemas

```typescript
import { createSchema, InferType } from '@belt/tools';

// Define schema
const TrainModel = createSchema({
  id: 'string',
  name: 'string',
  mileage: 'number',
  lastPM: 'date',
  tags: 'string[]',
  metadata: 'object?', // Optional generic object
});

// Infer TypeScript type
type Train = InferType<typeof TrainModel>;

// Parse and validate
const train = TrainModel.parse({
  id: 'T001',
  name: 'Red Line',
  mileage: 50000,
  lastPM: new Date('2025-01-01'),
  tags: ['metro', 'active'],
});

// Validate without parsing
if (TrainModel.isValid(data)) {
  // TypeScript knows data is Train
}

// Assert type (throws if invalid)
invariantType(TrainModel, data);
```

#### Complex Types

```typescript
import { createType } from '@belt/tools';

// Nested objects
const PMEventType = createType({
  properties: {
    trainId: 'string',
    scheduledDate: 'date',
    location: {
      properties: {
        facility: 'string',
        bay: 'number',
      },
    },
    tasks: {
      items: { // Array of objects
        properties: {
          code: 'string',
          duration: 'number',
          completed: 'boolean?',
        },
      },
    },
  },
});

// Enums
const StatusEnum = createType({
  enum: ['pending', 'in-progress', 'completed', 'cancelled'],
});

// Unions
const IDType = createType({
  union: ['string', 'number'],
});

// Records (key-value maps)
const ConfigType = createType({
  record: 'string', // Record<string, string>
});
```

#### List Parsing

```typescript
// Parse array of items
const trainList = TrainModel.list().parse([
  { id: 'T001', name: 'Red Line', mileage: 50000, lastPM: new Date(), tags: [] },
  { id: 'T002', name: 'Blue Line', mileage: 30000, lastPM: new Date(), tags: [] },
]);

// Parse array from nested path
const events = PMEventType.parseList(response, 'data.events');
```

---

### Date Utilities

Date manipulation and formatting using date-fns.

```typescript
import { formatDate, setDefaultDateLocale, ms } from '@belt/tools';
import { ptBR } from 'date-fns/locale';

// Format dates
formatDate(new Date(), 'yyyy-MM-dd'); // '2026-01-14'
formatDate(new Date(), 'MMM dd, yyyy'); // 'Jan 14, 2026'
formatDate('2026-01-14', 'dd/MM/yyyy'); // '14/01/2026'

// Set global locale
setDefaultDateLocale(ptBR);
formatDate(new Date(), 'MMMM'); // 'janeiro'

// Override locale for single call
import { enUS } from 'date-fns/locale';
formatDate(new Date(), 'MMMM', { locale: enUS }); // 'January'

// Time string conversion
ms('1s');       // 1000
ms('5m');       // 300000
ms('1h');       // 3600000
ms('2d');       // 172800000
ms('1w');       // 604800000
ms('1mo');      // ~2629800000
ms('1y');       // ~31557600000
ms('500ms');    // 500

// Use in configs
const CACHE_TTL = ms('5m');
const DEBOUNCE = ms('300ms');
const POLL_INTERVAL = ms('30s');
```

**Supported time units:** `ms`, `s`, `m`/`min`, `h`, `d`, `w`, `mo`/`mon`/`months`, `y`

---

### Object Utilities

Type-safe object manipulation with deep path access.

```typescript
import {
  getProperty,
  setProperty,
  objectKeys,
  objectEntries,
  objectValues,
  keyBy,
  isObject,
  assertObject,
  requireAll,
  deepFreeze,
} from '@belt/tools';

// Deep property access (type-safe)
const street = getProperty(user, 'address.street');
const city = getProperty(user, 'address.city', true); // Allow falsy values

// Set nested properties
setProperty(train, 'metadata.lastInspection', new Date());

// Object manipulation
const keys = objectKeys(train); // Type-safe keys
const entries = objectEntries(train); // Typed entries
const values = objectValues(train); // Typed values

// Array to object by key
const trainsById = keyBy(trains, 'id');
// Or with function
const trainsByName = keyBy(trains, (t) => t.name);

// Type guards
if (isObject(value)) {
  // value is UnknownRecord
}

// Assert object with no falsy values
const validated = requireAll({
  id: train.id,
  name: train.name,
  mileage: train.mileage,
});

// Deep freeze (immutability)
const frozen = deepFreeze(config);
```

**Path Examples:**
```typescript
type User = {
  id: string;
  profile: {
    address: {
      street: string;
      city: string;
    };
  };
};

// All paths are type-checked
getProperty(user, 'id');                    // ✓ string
getProperty(user, 'profile.address.city');  // ✓ string
getProperty(user, 'profile.invalid');       // ✗ Type error
```

---

### String Utilities

String manipulation with type inference.

```typescript
import { capitalize, isString, assertString } from '@belt/tools';

// Capitalize
capitalize('hello'); // 'Hello' (type: 'Hello')

// Type guards
if (isString(value)) {
  console.log(value.toUpperCase());
}

// Assertions
assertString(value);
assertString(value, { notEmpty: true });
assertString(value, { message: 'Name is required', notEmpty: true });
```

---

### Error Handling

Comprehensive error utilities with stack trace management.

```typescript
import {
  invariant,
  tryCatch,
  InvariantError,
  createErrorList,
} from '@belt/tools';

// Assertions
invariant(user.id, 'User ID is required');
invariant(trains.length > 0, 'No trains found');

// Safe error handling
const [error, result] = tryCatch(() => JSON.parse(data));
if (error) {
  console.error('Parse failed:', error.message);
} else {
  console.log('Success:', result);
}

// Collect multiple errors
const errors = createErrorList('Validation failed: ');
if (!train.id) errors.add('Missing ID');
if (!train.name) errors.add('Missing name');
if (train.mileage < 0) errors.add('Invalid mileage');
errors.check(); // Throws if any errors
```

---

### Type Utilities

Advanced TypeScript type helpers.

```typescript
import type {
  Paths,          // All dot-notation paths of object
  PathType,       // Type at specific path
  Compute,        // Flatten intersection types
  Writable,       // Remove readonly modifiers
  Falsy,          // Union of falsy values
  InferType,      // Infer type from schema
  UnknownRecord,  // { [key: string]: unknown }
  AnyRecord,      // { [key: string]: any }
  MaybePromise,   // T | Promise<T>
  MaybeArray,     // T | T[]
  PromiseValue,   // Extract Promise<T> → T
  Simplify,       // Flatten complex types
  Merge,          // Deep merge two types
  PartialFields,  // Make specific fields optional
  NullableToPartial, // Convert nullable to optional
  UnionToIntersection, // Union → Intersection
  CastUnknown,    // Cast if unknown
  SerializableOnly, // Only serializable fields
} from '@belt/tools';

// Example: Paths
type User = {
  id: string;
  profile: {
    address: {
      street: string;
    };
  };
};

type UserPaths = Paths<User>;
// 'id' | 'profile' | 'profile.address' | 'profile.address.street'

type StreetType = PathType<User, 'profile.address.street'>;
// string

// Example: Compute (flatten intersections)
type A = { a: number };
type B = { b: string };
type Flat = Compute<A & B>; // { a: number; b: string }

// Example: Writable
type ReadOnly = { readonly id: string; readonly name: string };
type Mutable = Writable<ReadOnly>; // { id: string; name: string }

// Example: PartialFields
type Train = { id: string; name: string; metadata: object };
type Optional = PartialFields<Train, ['metadata']>;
// { id: string; name: string; metadata?: object }
```

**Type Guards:**
```typescript
import { isFalsy } from '@belt/tools';
import type { Falsy } from '@belt/tools';

// All falsy values
const falsyValues: Falsy = false | '' | null | undefined | 0 | 0n | NaN;

if (isFalsy(value)) {
  // value is one of the falsy values
}
```

---

### Other Utilities

```typescript
import { delay, maskData, getTypeOf, createProxy } from '@belt/tools';

// Async delay
await delay(500); // Wait 500ms
await delay();    // Default 500ms

// Mask sensitive data for logging
const masked = maskData({
  password: 'secret123',
  email: 'user@example.com',
  nested: { token: 'abc123' },
});
// { password: 'String', email: 'String', nested: { token: 'String' } }

// Get type name
getTypeOf(null);           // 'Null'
getTypeOf(undefined);      // 'Undefined'
getTypeOf(new Date());     // 'Date'
getTypeOf({});             // 'Object'
getTypeOf([]);             // 'Array'
getTypeOf(NaN);            // 'NaN'

// Lazy initialization
const lazyConfig = createProxy(() => loadConfig());
// Config is only loaded on first access
```

